trans-unit.source: Supports the parsing and persisting of an expression-binding instance.
This class cannot be inherited.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.UI.ExpressionBinding"></xref> class.
A string indicating the name of the property of the object to which the expression parameter is applied.
A indicating the type of the property of the object to which the expression parameter is applied.
A string representing the expression's prefix value.
A string representing the value of the expression in its declarative syntax.
Determines whether the specified object is the same instance as the current <xref href="System.Web.UI.ExpressionBinding"></xref> object.
The object to compare with the current <xref href="System.Web.UI.ExpressionBinding"></xref>.
`true` if the specified object is the same instance as the current <xref href="System.Web.UI.ExpressionBinding"></xref>; otherwise, `false`.
Gets or sets a value of the expression in its declarative syntax.
A string that is used with the <xref href="System.Web.UI.ExpressionBinding.ExpressionPrefix"></xref> property to perform an action.
Gets or sets a value for the prefix of an expression in its declarative syntax.
A string that represents the expression prefix.
Gets a value indicating whether the expression was implicitly generated by the parser.
`true` if the expression was implicitly generated by the parser; otherwise, `false`.
Serves as a hash function for the current <xref href="System.Web.UI.ExpressionBinding"></xref> object; suitable for hashing algorithms and data structures, such as a hash table.
A hash code for the current <xref href="System.Web.UI.ExpressionBinding"></xref>.

Gets an object representing the data from an expression as created through the <xref href="System.Web.Compilation.ExpressionBuilder.ParseExpression(System.String,System.Type,System.Web.Compilation.ExpressionBuilderContext)"></xref> method.

The object representing the data from an expression as created by calling the <xref href="System.Web.Compilation.ExpressionBuilder.ParseExpression(System.String,System.Type,System.Web.Compilation.ExpressionBuilderContext)"></xref> method.
Gets a value indicating the name of the property of the object to which the expression is applied.
A value that represents the name of the property of the object to which the expression is applied.
Gets a value indicating the <xref href="System.Type"></xref> of the property of the object to which the expression is applied.
The <xref href="System.Type"></xref> of the property of the object to which the expression is applied.
